  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">This letter is about the contributions from Cork, Ireland, to the Boston anti-slavery fair. Isabel Jennings requests that the names of the contributors be published and that Maria Weston Chapman send a published account of the fair for distribution among the contributors. Five copies of the Liberty Bell are desired for the officers of the society and one especially devoted worker.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">This letter is signed by Isabel Jennings and Mary Mannix, both secretaries of the female anti-slavery society in Cork, Ireland.</subfield>
